title: Mirvac profit rises 36pct on strong market
text:
Thu, Aug 13, 2015, 9:46 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 14 mins. Mirvac profit rises 36pct on strong market AAP – 4 minutes 26 seconds ago Recommend Print 
Property developer Mirvac has lifted full year profit 36 per cent thanks to the still strong housing market, particularly in Sydney and Melbourne. 
Net profit for the 12 months to June 30 rose to $609.9 million from $447.3 million thanks to a nine per cent increase in total revenue to $2.152 billion. 
Operating profit excluding one-offs was up four per cent to $454.8 million, which was at the top end of the company's guidance. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Fairfax profit down, digital income soars AAP
